{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, inference or training tasks deferred in response to high electricity prices may be rescheduled simultaneously once prices fall, leading to secondary demand peaks or rebound effects that stress the grid.",
    "Moreover, AI data center operators are relatively insensitive to electricity prices.",
    "As noted in [126], these facilities have high sunk capital costs, and the workloads they run are highly lucrative.",
    "As a result, the opportunity cost of deferring training or inference tasks can outweigh potential savings from energy arbitrage.",
    "Therefore, relying on price signals alone may be insufficient to drive effective load shifting."
  ]
}